          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".The experiments were performed using",
                "conventional delta-E-E surface barrier detector",
                "techniques. Two telescopes were used during the",
                "experiments. The thicknesses of the delta-E and",
                "E detectors was 100 mum and 1000 mum, respectively."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".The incident beam current was continuously",
                "monitored by a Ge(Li) .",
                "The ratio of the deuteron yield elastically scattered",
                "into the monitor counter to the integrated charge",
                "collected in a Faraday cup was used to ensure the",
                "accuracy of the determination of the relative cross",
                "sections at various angles, this ratio was always",
                "constant within 5%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.The absolute cross section were determined",
                "by the integrated charge only."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*EN-RSL-FW*.An overall energy resolution of typically",
                " 350 keV (FWHM)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".DWBA calculations, the alpha spectroscopic",
                " factors.",
                " Typical energy spectrum of Ne-22(d,Li-6)O-18 reaction,",
                "taken at Ang(lab)=15-degree is shown on fig.1."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A gas cell filled with Ne gas isotopically enriched",
                "to 95.3% of Ne-22 was used as target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".The beam intensity ranged from 10 nA to 1.3 muA",
                "on the target, depending on the reaction angle."
              ]
            }
          ],
